headline: Analysis-Trump's vision for a twin-engine F-55 fighter jet faces reality check
summary: WASHINGTON (Reuters) -U.S. President Donald Trump's vision of a new, twin-engine version of Lockheed Martin's F-35 fighter jet may need to be scaled back due to cost and engineering realities, according to two people familiar with the matter.  Speaking in Doha last month, Trump said the new "F-55" would feature "two engines and a super upgrade on the F-35."  Trump was not shown a twin-engine redesign of the F-35, the two sources said, speaking on condition of anonymity due to the sensitivity of the matter.
